import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='u', y='v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True, color='blue', label='u')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of u?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.axvline(data['v'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['v'].median():.2f}")

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.boxplot(x=data['u'], ax=ax)
    avg_u = data['u'].mean()
    ax.axvline(avg_u, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_u:.2f}')
    ax.set_title('What is the average value of u?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('u')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='v', ax=ax)
    avg_v = data['v'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_v, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_v:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average value of v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
